## Next Steps

*   Working Group Chairs and Authors will finalize the discussed Pull Requests for both documents and push new versions.
*   Once ADs clear the "discusses," the documents will be submitted for ISG approval.
*   Upon ISG approval, the documents will enter the RFC Editor's queue, anticipated to take 2-3 months before publication as RFCs, including an Auth48 review phase.
*   The Working Group will proceed with work on the MLS Extensions and Federation documents, with an IETF 116 session requested to discuss progress.
*   Consideration of MLSv2 and other long-term topics will follow initial publication.
*   The three unaddressed ART area comments (extensibility, DS implementation impact, client removal difficulty) will be kept in mind for potential future discussions or separate informational drafts.